#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""sable-merge-gate — the merge-preview ci-verify gate (SABLE-o9aa / h853 option b).

The chuck-side half of the SABLE-h853 test-protocol flip. Once h853 lands,
workers push scoped evidence only and stop running the full suite locally, so
the AUTHORITATIVE full-suite run moves to merge time. This gate is that run.

The load-bearing property is BYTE-IDENTICAL PROMOTION: what CI validates must be
exactly what lands on the integration branch, so the flow NEVER re-merges after
green — it promotes the same commit object it tested.

  1. rev-parse the pushed worker ref            (chuck's standing verification)
  2. build the MERGE-PREVIEW commit with no working tree:
       git merge-tree --write-tree <base> <branch>   -> merged tree (exit 1 = conflict -> exit 22, delegate)
       git commit-tree <tree> -p <base> -p <branch>   -> preview commit
  3. push the preview commit to  ci-verify/<bead>-<previewsha7>
  4. READ the verdict for the preview SHA; wait only if there isn't one yet
  5. GREEN  -> push the SAME object to the integration branch (fast-forward),
     then assert remote base tip SHA == preview SHA (integrity; exit 4 if not).
     Delete the ci-verify ref, append evidence to the bead.
  6. RED    -> NO promotion. Capture run URL, delete ci-verify ref, notify the
     lane manager, append evidence. Exit 20.
  6b. CANCELLED (run conclusion=='cancelled', not a test failure) -> RETRYABLE,
     never RED: a mid-flight cancellation (a concurrent sweep deleting the
     in-flight ref, a manual cancel, or the per-ref concurrency group pre-empting
     it) is not a content defect, so the author is told NOTHING to fix. Delete
     the ci-verify ref, notify the manager to rebuild preview + re-gate, append
     evidence. Exit 24 (like BASE-MOVED/23 — retry-safe). SABLE-sc24.
  7. ACTIONS-DOWN (no run appears within grace / API error) -> BLOCK: no
     promotion, notify lincoln. Only bypass is --override <url> (recorded on the
     bead). NEVER fall back to a local suite run (ayzv-class env brittleness).
     Exit 21.

── MODULE LAYOUT (SABLE-jd5fj.3) ────────────────────────────────────────────
This file is the CLI. The gate itself lives in three modules beside it, in
dependency order (a DAG — nothing imports "upward"):

  sable_gate_classify_lib.py   PURE. Ref naming, the shared idempotency key, the
                               sweep age predicate, and the exit-code taxonomy:
                               what an Actions conclusion MEANS and which code
                               that meaning carries. No I/O at all.
  sable_gate_git_lib.py        The subprocess seam: SABLE_MG_GIT/_GH/_BD/_NOTIFY,
                               `_git`, and repo-identity resolution.
  sable_gate_preview_lib.py    Builds previews, kicks ci-verify refs, READS
                               verdicts, sweeps orphans. Never promotes.
  sable_gate_promote_lib.py    Consumes a verdict and promotes (or refuses).
                               The only writer to the integration branch.
  sable_gate_budget_lib.py     Per-tier duration budget breach detection +
                               idempotent bead filing (SABLE-cmar4.4). Called
                               by promote, wrapped around the acquire_verdict
                               call — the one place the gate's own wall-clock
                               for the merge_preview tier is observable.
  sable_footprint_lib.py       Changed-path footprints and the disjointness
                               test (SABLE-jd5fj.4). Evidence only — it decides
                               nothing about a promotion.
  sable_snapshot_lib.py        The green snapshot's classifier + freeze/
                               quarantine state (SABLE-jd5fj.5). promote reads
                               its freeze flag as the FIRST thing it does and
                               refuses with exit 25 — a mechanical deny path,
                               not a convention. Nothing here imports the gate
                               back; see bin/sable-snapshot for the runner.
  sable_coverage_floor_lib.py  PURE detection + decision (pruning-diff
                               detection, named-override parsing, the
                               allow/deny table) plus the one I/O function that
                               shells out to .github/ci/diff-cover-gate.sh in a
                               throwaway worktree (SABLE-cmar4.5). promote
                               reads it right after the freeze check and
                               refuses with exit 27 — same mechanical-deny
                               shape as the freeze, one bead later.

── OPTIMISTIC DISJOINT PROMOTION (SABLE-jd5fj.4) ────────────────────────────
When the base moves between a preview and its promote, the CI-green object is
no longer what would land. Before jd5fj.4 that was always exit 23: rebuild and
re-gate through a full CI cycle. Now the gate asks a second question first — are
the base-move's changed paths DISJOINT from the branch's? — and if they are, it
re-verifies the REAL COMBINED TREE with the cmar4 impact tier instead of a full
re-preview. Green promotes that combined object; red ejects on exit 20; an
impact tier that cannot answer falls back to exit 23.

That path is entered from an ADOPTION MISS too (SABLE-kzi1a), not only from a
base that moved mid-gate. Chuck promotes SERIALLY and is the only writer to the
integration branch, so the base cannot move DURING a promote — the mid-gate entry
is unreachable in the real operating model (measured: 0 optimistic promotions in
157, and 0 across a 15-worker burst that queued 11 branches). What the queue does
produce is the same situation one step earlier: each merge moves the base and
invalidates the push-time preview of every branch still queued, so the next
promote finds a COMPLETED GREEN run for a preview whose base has moved. It now
takes that to the same decision — same footprint computation, same mandatory
impact tier on the real combined tree — instead of discarding the green run and
paying for a fresh one. When the assessment does not license the cheap path, the
promote simply builds a preview the pre-kick way, which is what it did before.

Disjointness is NECESSARY, NEVER SUFFICIENT (locked contract SABLE-djopw):
file-disjoint changes break each other semantically all the time, so a disjoint
verdict buys a CHEAPER re-test, never a skipped one. Footprints follow renames,
INCLUDE deletions, treat lockfiles and committed generated artifacts as
non-disjoint sentinels, and are widened (never narrowed) by the bead's declared
footprint. Two invariants are enumerated exhaustively in
bin/test_promote_decision.py: no promote path where the base moved and the
footprints are not proven disjoint and nothing re-verified; and every promotion
pushes exactly the object some verifier attested. SABLE_MG_OPTIMISTIC=0 restores
the pre-jd5fj.4 behaviour exactly.

The split was made because this file had grown into a god-module carrying a
safety-critical write path (locked smell risk, relates SABLE-hhw7t), and because
the parallel-preview flow needs a VERDICT to be a value that can be computed at
push time and consumed later — not a side effect reachable only by running
promote end to end. Module boundaries are asserted, not just described:
bin/test_merge_gate_modules.py fails if promote logic reappears in the preview
module or if the taxonomy drifts.

PATCHING NOTE for tests: the seams live in the module that DEFINES them. Patch
`sable_gate_git_lib._git`, not a re-export here — every module calls the seams
module-qualified precisely so one patch reaches the whole gate. The private
seams are deliberately NOT re-exported below, so that a patch aimed at the wrong
object fails loudly (AttributeError) instead of silently doing nothing.

── PER-TIER DURATION BUDGET (SABLE-cmar4.4) ─────────────────────────────────
promote measures its own wall-clock spent reading/waiting for the verdict
(sable_gate_preview_lib.acquire_verdict) and checks it against the
merge_preview tier's budget declared in .github/ci/test-tiers.sh (the cmar4.1
SSOT). This is a per-TIER-TOTAL measurement, never per-test (locked,
split-invariant): splitting a slow suite into faster pieces cannot evade a
breach, only reducing the tier's real total can. A breach WARNs on stderr and
auto-files exactly ONE suite-optimization bead via sable_gate_budget_lib,
idempotent on (tier, budget_sec) — the budget value doubles as its own
version, so bumping the SSOT's number for a tier is what a "version bump"
IS, and re-runs against an unedited, still-open breach file nothing new. Never
blocks or fails a promotion; an unresolvable budget silently skips the check.

── PARALLEL PREVIEWS ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
N previews on N distinct ci-verify/<bead>-<sha7> refs run CONCURRENTLY:
ci-verify.yml's concurrency group is `ci-verify-${{ github.ref }}`, so distinct
refs are distinct groups and cancel-in-progress never reaches across them. The
ceiling is GitHub's 20 concurrent jobs per account — beyond that previews QUEUE
(latency), they do not fail. hooks/test/test-parallel-previews.sh pins both.

Base resolution is ALWAYS fully qualified (refs/remotes/<remote>/<branch> via
`git rev-parse --verify`); bare `origin/<branch>` is refused because a stray
local branch named `origin` makes it ambiguous (SABLE-92kc-adjacent).

Cleanup: the ci-verify ref is deleted on BOTH green and red paths. `sable-merge-
gate sweep` deletes orphaned ci-verify/* refs older than a threshold in HOURS
(default 6) for the crash-between-push-and-cleanup case. The sweep NEVER reaps a
ref whose Actions run is still in-flight, however old the ref's commit date —
deleting the ref cancels the run, which is exactly the spurious-RED failure
SABLE-sc24 exists to prevent.

Prior art: the throwaway-branch pattern from the 754r verification (ci-verify-754r).

Usage:
  sable-merge-gate promote --bead <id> --branch <worker-branch> [--base <branch>]
                           [--repo <path>] [--remote <name>] [--manager <name>]
                           [--override <reason>]   # actions-down human bypass ONLY,
                                                    # reason recorded; never for a known-red
  sable-merge-gate preview --branch <worker-branch> [--base <branch>]
                           [--repo <path>] [--remote <name>]
  sable-merge-gate verdict --branch <worker-branch> [--base <branch>] [--json]
                           [--repo <path>] [--remote <name>]
  sable-merge-gate sweep   [--max-age-hours N] [--repo <path>] [--remote <name>]
  sable-merge-gate promote-budget [--json | --seconds]
  sable-merge-gate --help

`promote-budget` (SABLE-w0zjm) exists for the code that WRAPS this one. A promote
may legitimately spend an impact-tier queue wait PLUS the tier's own budget, so
any enclosing `timeout` must be derived from that sum rather than copied — the
copy was 900s at the merge seat, the same number as the tier budget, sized back
when the tier essentially never ran.

The `preview` entrypoint (SABLE-jd5fj.1) is the KICK half of promote: it builds
the merge-preview commit and pushes the ci-verify ref — and then RETURNS, at
once, without waiting for the Actions run. hooks/multi-manager/post-push-merge-
notify.sh fires it in the background on a confirmed worker push, so the verdict
is already computing by the time Chuck wakes to merge.

The `verdict` entrypoint (SABLE-jd5fj.3) is the READ half: it reports what CI
already concluded about merging <branch> onto <base> — green / red / retry /
pending / none — in ONE API call, without building, pushing, waiting, or
promoting. It is the first step of Chuck's flow (read-verdict -> sequence ->
promote): read N verdicts for N workers' concurrent previews, sequence the green
ones into the serialized promote lane, leave the rest. `promote` then consumes
that same stored verdict in seconds instead of constructing and waiting.

The kick and promote meet at a SHARED IDEMPOTENCY KEY (preview_kick_ref): the
kicked ref is named from the (base_sha, branch_sha) pair, NOT from the
nondeterministic preview commit's own SHA (commit-tree stamps a committer date,
so rebuilding the same merge twice yields two different SHAs — and two different
refs, i.e. two CI runs). Because the key is a pure function of the two parents,
promote can look for an already-kicked ref and ADOPT it instead of building a
second preview: same parents => same merge result, and the object it promotes is
still byte-identical to the object CI tested. Adoption is a pure optimization —
it verifies the kicked commit's parents against the freshly resolved base/branch
SHAs and falls through to the normal build on ANY mismatch, error, or absence, so
a stale or missing kick can never change an outcome.

Base resolution (SABLE-dtp1): an explicit --base flag wins outright; else
SABLE_MG_BASE wins; else the base is resolved via resolve_integration_branch()
against --repo — the same precedence hooks/multi-manager/lib-identity.sh's
sable_resolve_integration_branch hands the pre-push hook (git config
sable.integrationBranch > repo .sable file > SABLE_INTEGRATION_BRANCH /
SABLE_BASE_BRANCH env > "main") — so the gate never targets a base the
pre-push hook wouldn't recognize as this repo's integration branch.

Environment seams (overridable; defaults are the production commands so the flow
is unit-testable without real git / gh / bd):
  SABLE_MG_BASE  base override (see above)                SABLE_MG_REMOTE (origin)
  SABLE_MG_REPO  repo path (default $PWD)                 SABLE_MG_GIT    (git)
  SABLE_MG_GH    gh command (gh)                          SABLE_MG_BD     (bd)
  SABLE_MG_NOTIFY notify command (sable-msg)              SABLE_MG_POLL   (20)
  SABLE_MG_TIMEOUT Actions wait secs (default: this repo's merge_preview
                   tier budget from .github/ci/test-tiers.sh if present,
                   else 1800 — SABLE-cmar4.1)                SABLE_MG_GRACE  first-run grace secs (300)
  SABLE_MG_SWEEP_HOURS orphan age hours (6)               SABLE_MG_GH_TIMEOUT per-gh-call secs (30, SABLE-7wyl)
  SABLE_MG_OPTIMISTIC  1 (SABLE-jd5fj.4; 0 = every base-move is a full re-preview)
  SABLE_MG_IMPACT_TIMEOUT per-command secs for the combined-tree impact tier (900)
  SABLE_MG_IMPACT      impact-tier command override (testing seam; run in the
                       combined-tree worktree with the changed paths appended)
  SABLE_MG_IMPACT_SERIALIZE 1 (SABLE-jd5fj.13; 0 = let concurrent promotes run
                       the local impact tier at the same time. They false-RED
                       each other when you do — the iron-rule suites share live
                       bd/settings/worker state. Test seam, not an operator knob.)
  SABLE_MG_IMPACT_LOCK_TIMEOUT secs to wait for that lock (3600); giving up is an
                       impact-tier ERROR -> full re-preview, never a promotion
  SABLE_MG_IMPACT_LOCK path override for the lock file (default: the merge-gate
                       state dir); SABLE_MG_IMPACT_WINDOW_LOG likewise for the
                       tier start/end window log

Exit codes:
  0 promoted / preview kicked / verdict read / sweep ok    2 usage   3 precondition failed
  20 ci red, not promoted   21 actions-down / blocked (needs --override)
  22 merge-preview conflict (delegate to author)
  23 tip moved during gate and the move was not provably disjoint (or the impact
     tier could not answer) — rebuild preview + re-gate (retry-safe)
  24 ci-verify run cancelled mid-flight — rebuild preview + re-gate (retry-safe, SABLE-sc24)
  25 green-snapshot FREEZE in force — the integration branch is deterministically
     red, so NO merge promotes until a green snapshot (or a recorded
     `sable-snapshot unfreeze`) lifts it (SABLE-jd5fj.5)
  27 COVERAGE FLOOR — a pruning diff (removed test fn / newly-skipped test /
     deleted test file) with no carried, passing coverage-delta check
     (.github/ci/diff-cover-gate.sh) — needs the check to pass, or a named
     `--coverage-override <reason>` (SABLE-cmar4.5). NOTE: 26 is reserved by
     bin/sable-snapshot's own taxonomy (EXIT_QUARANTINED) — a DIFFERENT tool,
     but 25/EXIT_FROZEN is deliberately shared between the two, so this picks
     the next free number rather than reusing 26 with a different meaning.
  4 integrity abort (base tip != preview SHA after promote)
"""
from __future__ import annotations

import argparse
import json
import os
import sys

sys.path.insert(0, os.path.dirname(os.path.realpath(__file__)))

import sable_footprint_lib as footprint_lib          # noqa: E402
import sable_gate_classify_lib as classify           # noqa: E402
import sable_gate_git_lib as git_lib                 # noqa: E402
import sable_gate_preview_lib as preview_lib         # noqa: E402
import sable_gate_promote_lib as promote_lib         # noqa: E402
import sable_snapshot_lib as snapshot_lib            # noqa: E402

# Public API re-exports. These are the names OTHER tools import from this file
# (bin/sable-reconcile-handoffs reuses the resolver, the ref-qualifier and the
# kick as a single source of truth), plus the pure helpers external unit tests
# call. The private subprocess seams are NOT re-exported — see the PATCHING NOTE
# in the module docstring.
GateError = classify.GateError
preview_ref_name = classify.preview_ref_name
preview_kick_key = classify.preview_kick_key
preview_kick_ref = classify.preview_kick_ref
is_orphan = classify.is_orphan
qualify_remote_ref = classify.qualify_remote_ref
classify_conclusion = classify.classify_conclusion
Verdict = classify.Verdict
resolve_integration_branch = git_lib.resolve_integration_branch
resolve_base = git_lib.resolve_base
resolve_commit = git_lib.resolve_commit
default_mg_timeout = git_lib.default_mg_timeout
build_preview = preview_lib.build_preview
adopt_kicked_preview = preview_lib.adopt_kicked_preview
kick_preview = preview_lib.kick_preview
read_verdict = preview_lib.read_verdict
acquire_verdict = preview_lib.acquire_verdict
wait_for_ci = preview_lib.wait_for_ci
ref_has_inflight_run = preview_lib.ref_has_inflight_run
sweep = preview_lib.sweep
promote = promote_lib.promote
cleanup_after_merge = promote_lib.cleanup_after_merge
decide_promotion = promote_lib.decide_promotion
run_impact_tier = promote_lib.run_impact_tier
impact_budget = promote_lib.impact_budget
format_impact_budget = promote_lib.format_impact_budget
assess_footprints = footprint_lib.assess
assert_not_frozen = promote_lib.assert_not_frozen
read_freeze = snapshot_lib.read_freeze


def main(argv: list[str] | None = None) -> int:
    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(prog="sable-merge-gate")
    sub = parser.add_subparsers(dest="command", required=True)

    pp = sub.add_parser("promote")
    pp.add_argument("--bead", required=True)
    pp.add_argument("--branch", required=True)
    pp.add_argument("--base", default=None,
                    help="integration branch to promote onto; default resolves via "
                         "SABLE_MG_BASE env, else this repo's own integration branch "
                         "(resolve_base/resolve_integration_branch — SABLE-dtp1)")
    pp.add_argument("--repo", default=os.environ.get("SABLE_MG_REPO", os.getcwd()))
    # SABLE-dtp1 re-examined SABLE_MG_REMOTE's "origin" default alongside --base:
    # unlike the integration branch, no repo-aware remote-name override exists
    # anywhere in the fleet (lib-identity.sh, sable-spawn-worker, pre-push hook
    # all assume "origin" too) — nothing to fix here.
    pp.add_argument("--remote", default=os.environ.get("SABLE_MG_REMOTE", "origin"))
    pp.add_argument("--manager", default="lincoln")
    pp.add_argument("--override", default=None, metavar="REASON",
                    help="actions-down human bypass ONLY; the reason is required and recorded on the bead. "
                         "Not for bypassing a known-red run.")
    pp.add_argument("--coverage-override", default=None, metavar="REASON",
                    dest="coverage_override",
                    help="named-reason bypass of the coverage floor on a PRUNING diff only "
                         "(SABLE-cmar4.5) — a diff with no removed test fn / newly-skipped "
                         "test / deleted test file never needs this. Recorded on the bead. "
                         "Mirrors the 'Model override: <reason>' pattern; also accepted as a "
                         "'Coverage override: <reason>' line in this flag's own value.")

    # SABLE-jd5fj.1 kick entrypoint. No --bead: the post-push hook that fires
    # this knows the branch it just confirmed, not the bead behind it, and a kick
    # writes no bead evidence anyway.
    pv = sub.add_parser("preview")
    pv.add_argument("--branch", required=True)
    pv.add_argument("--base", default=None,
                    help="integration branch to preview onto; same resolution as promote")
    pv.add_argument("--repo", default=os.environ.get("SABLE_MG_REPO", os.getcwd()))
    pv.add_argument("--remote", default=os.environ.get("SABLE_MG_REMOTE", "origin"))

    # SABLE-jd5fj.3 read entrypoint. Also no --bead: a verdict is a property of
    # the (base, branch) merge, which is what the shared idempotency key names.
    pj = sub.add_parser("verdict")
    pj.add_argument("--branch", required=True)
    pj.add_argument("--base", default=None,
                    help="integration branch to read the verdict against; same resolution as promote")
    pj.add_argument("--repo", default=os.environ.get("SABLE_MG_REPO", os.getcwd()))
    pj.add_argument("--remote", default=os.environ.get("SABLE_MG_REMOTE", "origin"))
    pj.add_argument("--json", action="store_true",
                    help="machine-readable single-line JSON (chuck's read-verdict step)")

    ps = sub.add_parser("sweep")
    ps.add_argument("--max-age-hours", type=float,
                    default=float(os.environ.get("SABLE_MG_SWEEP_HOURS", "6")))
    ps.add_argument("--repo", default=os.environ.get("SABLE_MG_REPO", os.getcwd()))
    ps.add_argument("--remote", default=os.environ.get("SABLE_MG_REMOTE", "origin"))

    # SABLE-w0zjm. The gate's own worst-case promote wall-clock, so an operator
    # wrapper DERIVES its timeout instead of keeping a second copy of the number.
    # Named promote-budget, not budget, because sable_gate_budget_lib already owns
    # "budget" for a different thing entirely (per-tier CI DURATION budgets,
    # SABLE-cmar4.4). Takes no --repo: every input is an env var, so this answers
    # without touching git and can be called from anywhere, including the wrapper
    # that has not chosen a repo yet.
    pb = sub.add_parser("promote-budget",
                        help="print the worst-case promote wall-clock an enclosing "
                             "timeout must exceed")
    pbg = pb.add_mutually_exclusive_group()
    pbg.add_argument("--json", action="store_true",
                     help="machine-readable single-line JSON with every component")
    pbg.add_argument("--seconds", action="store_true",
                     help="just the recommended enclosing timeout, as a bare integer: "
                          "timeout \"$(sable-merge-gate promote-budget --seconds)\" ...")

    # SABLE-jd5fj.8. Refreshes the gate-owned persisted warm .testmondata
    # (see sable_gate_promote_lib's module comment on _warm_testmondata_path)
    # by running the full bin/ suite with --testmon-noselect, same as CI's
    # .github/ci/testmon-cache-warm.sh — meant to be run periodically or by
    # an operator, NOT by the gate itself on every promote.
    pw = sub.add_parser("warm-testmon-cache",
                        help="refresh the gate-owned warm .testmondata used by the "
                             "combined-tree impact tier's pytest half")
    pw.add_argument("--repo", default=os.environ.get("SABLE_MG_REPO", os.getcwd()))

    args = parser.parse_args(argv)
    try:
        if args.command == "promote":
            base = git_lib.resolve_base(args.base, args.repo)
            return promote_lib.promote(args.bead, args.branch, base, args.repo,
                                       args.remote, args.manager, args.override,
                                       args.coverage_override)
        if args.command == "preview":
            base = git_lib.resolve_base(args.base, args.repo)
            return preview_lib.kick_preview(args.branch, base, args.repo, args.remote)
        if args.command == "verdict":
            base = git_lib.resolve_base(args.base, args.repo)
            return preview_lib.report_verdict(args.branch, base, args.repo,
                                              args.remote, args.json)
        if args.command == "sweep":
            return preview_lib.sweep(args.repo, args.remote, args.max_age_hours)
        if args.command == "promote-budget":
            budget = promote_lib.impact_budget()
            if args.seconds:
                print(budget["recommended_wrapper_timeout_s"])
            elif args.json:
                print(json.dumps(budget, sort_keys=True))
            else:
                print(promote_lib.format_impact_budget(budget))
            return 0
        if args.command == "warm-testmon-cache":
            return promote_lib.warm_gate_testmon_cache(args.repo)
    except classify.GateError as e:
        print(f"sable-merge-gate: {e}", file=sys.stderr)
        return e.code
    return 2


if __name__ == "__main__":
    sys.exit(main())
